'''Dr. Abdul Hamid Bahij''' ({{lang-ps|'''ډاکټر عبدالحميد بهيج'''}}), is an Afghan [[Physician|medical doctor]], writer, translator and [[dictionary]] writer.<ref name="Philosophical Dictionary">{{Cite book|title=Inglisī, Puṣhto falsafe qāmūs|last1=|first1=|authorlink=|coauthors=|volume=|year=2005|publisher=Danish Publishing Association|location=Kabul or Peshawar|isbn=|page=|pages=326|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IY9pGwAACAAJ&dq=Abdul+Hamid+Bahij&hl=en&ei=hELyTdqdO4boOayl4JoD&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CDEQ6AEwAA|accessdate=June 10, 2011}}</ref><ref name="Afghanistan analyst">{{Cite web |url=http://afghanistan-analyst.org/PashtoDictionaries.aspx |title=Pashto dictionaries |author=Dr. Abdul Hamid Bahij and the Academy of Sciences of Afghanistan 2008. Pashto-English Dictionary. Kabul: Danish Publishing Association. Provides translations of ~17,000 Pashto words into English. |publisher=The Afghanistan analyst, an online resource for Researching Afghanistan |year=2008 |accessdate=June 10, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110811051354/http://afghanistan-analyst.org/PashtoDictionaries.aspx |archivedate=August 11, 2011 }}</ref><ref name="Shahbookco">{{Cite web|url=http://www.shahmbookco.com/booklists/english/dictionaries.pdf |title=Dictionaries and Language Related, number 67, 68 and 133 on the list |publisher=shahmbookco.com |year=2006 |accessdate=June 13, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120325052233/http://www.shahmbookco.com/booklists/english/dictionaries.pdf |archivedate=March 25, 2012 }}</ref><ref name="Bahij's Medical Dictionary">{{cite web|url=http://nzdl.sadl.uleth.ca/cgi-bin/library.cgi?e=d-00000-00---off-0areu--00-0----0-10-0---0---0direct-10---4-------0-1l--11-en-50---20-about---00-0-1-00-0-0-11-1-0utfZz-8-00&a=d&c=areu&cl=CL5.9&d=HASH6380a90f0d562f01604b60&l=prs&nl=1 |title=Bahij's medical dictionary, English-Pashto, by Abdul Hamid Bahij. Peshawar: Danish Publishing Association, 2006. |author=Abdul Hamid Bahij |publisher=Afghanistan Research and Evaluation Unit |year=2011 |accessdate=June 13, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110823125528/http://nzdl.sadl.uleth.ca/cgi-bin/library.cgi?e=d-00000-00---off-0areu--00-0----0-10-0---0---0direct-10---4-------0-1l--11-en-50---20-about---00-0-1-00-0-0-11-1-0utfZz-8-00&a=d&c=areu&cl=CL5.9&d=HASH6380a90f0d562f01604b60&l=prs&nl=1 |archivedate=August 23, 2011 }}</ref>
==Early life== Abdul Hamid Bahij Osmani was born on March 6, 1979, in the village of Bedmushk, [[Jaghatu District (Wardak)|Jaghatu]] district of [[Wardak province]], Afghanistan. As the son of Ghulam Habib and grandson of Khoshdil.
==Education== Hamid gained his primary and secondary educations in the beautiful city of [[Peshawar]]. He went for his high education to [[Kabul Medical University]]. He gained his doctor from Kabul Medical University in the year 2006. Hamid is now concurrently busy with his study of German language at the Institute of [[Goethe]].
==Works==
His dictionary, with around 17,0000 Pashto words into English, is published by the Danish Publishings Association in 2008 and reprinted in 2009.<ref name="Afghanistan analyst"/>
=== Published works === Bahij has published 22 books of which 5 of them are dictionaries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pajhwok.com/en/node/59950 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-06-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120328034841/http://www.pajhwok.com/en/node/59950 |archivedate=March 28, 2012 |df=mdy }}</ref> The following list contains some of his published books; #'''Bahij's Political Dictionary''', is a Political English-Pashto dictionary of 410/411 pages and is published in year 2005.<ref name="Shahbookco"/> #'''English-Pashto Philosophical Dictionary''', is an English-Pashto philosophical dictionary of 323 pages and is published in the year 2005.<ref name="Philosophical Dictionary"/><ref name="Shahbookco"/> #'''Bahij's Medical Dictionary''', is a medical English-Pashto dictionary of 1206 pages and is published in the year 2006.<ref name="Shahbookco"/><ref name="Bahij's Medical Dictionary"/> #'''Medical Terminology''', 360 pages. #'''Da baran pa zhaba (on rains language)''', based on speeches of Jabrankhel Jabran. #'''Mathematics and Physical Science''', for twelfth class. #'''Triangle''', for eleventh class #'''Mathematics''', for eleventh class. #Dr. Abdul Hamid Bahij and the Academy of Sciences of Afghanistan 2008. '''Pashto-English Dictionary'''. Kabul: Danish Publishing Association.<ref>https://www.amazon.com/dp/B004S8UIOS</ref> With over 150 thousands (150000) words. #'''Bahij English-Pashto Dictionary''', 380 pages and published in year 2008.<ref>http://www.afghandost.com/products.php?product=Pashto-%252d-English-Dictionary#</ref>
