{{One source|date=April 2013}} {{Infobox language |name=Levantine Arabic Sign Language |altname=Syro-Palestinian Sign Language |region=[[Levant]] |speakers= ?<!--no speaker numbers in the Ethnologue 18--> |familycolor = sign language |fam1=[[Arab Sign Language family]] |fam2=Iraqi–Levantine? |dia1=Jordanian Sign Language (LIU) |dia2=Palestinian Sign Language |dia3=Syrian Sign Language |dia4=Lebanese Sign Language |iso3=jos |iso3comment=(Jordanian Sign Language) |glotto=none |glotto2=jord1238 |glottoname2=Jordanian SL |glottorefname2=Jordanian Sign Language }}
'''Levantine Arabic Sign Language''', also known as '''Syro-Palestinian Sign Language''',{{cn|date=March 2015}} is the [[deaf sign language]] of [[Jordan]], [[State of Palestine|Palestine]], [[Syria]], and [[Lebanon]]. Although there are significant differences in vocabulary between the four states, this is not much greater than regional differences within the states, their grammar is quite uniform, and mutual intelligibility is high, indicating that they are dialects of a single language (Hendriks 2008).[https://www.lotpublications.nl/Documents/193_fulltext.pdf]
The language typically goes by the name of the country, as so: * Jordanian SL: لغة الإشارة الأردنية ''Lughat il-Ishārah il-Urduniyyah'' (LIU) * Lebanese SL: لغة الإشارات اللبنانية ''Lughat al-Ishārāt al-Lubnāniyyah'' (LIL) * Palestinian SL: لغة الاشارات الفلسطينية ''Lughat al-Ishārāt al-Filisṭīniyyah'' (LIF) * Syrian SL: لغة الإشارة السورية ''Lughat il-Ishārah il-Sūriyyah'' (LIS)
