{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox person | name = Sonia Deepti | image = Sonia Deepti in the 9th Annual Day celebrations of Rainbow Concept School, Mahabubnagar, Telangana State (cropped).jpg | imagesize = 220px | caption = Sonia Deepti at the 9th Annual Day celebrations of Rainbow Concept School, Mahabubnagar. | birth_name = Sonia Deepti | birth_place = [[Hyderabad]], [[Telangana]], India | occupation = [[Actress]] | years_active = 2007–present }}
'''Sonia Deepti''' (born 29 July 1984)<ref>{{cite web|title=Sonia Deepti profile|url=http://www.veethi.com/india-people/sonia_deepti-profile-3710-14.htm|accessdate=3 September 2014}}</ref> is an Indian film actress, who has mostly appeared in Telugu films. Her debut performance as Shravs in the 2007 [[Sekhar Kammula]] film ''[[Happy Days (2007 film)|Happy Days]]'' won her the [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress – Telugu]].
==Career== Sonia was born and brought up in [[Hyderabad]], [[Telangana]].<ref name="idlebrain">{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/news/2000march20/chitchat-sonia.html |title=Sonia interview - chitchat - Telugu film actress |publisher=Idlebrain.com |date=2008-01-04 |accessdate=2016-12-04}}</ref> After finishing her studies with a degree in [[computer applications]], she worked as a [[software engineer]] in an IT company for three years, before stepping into acting.<ref name="idlebrain"/> At an event, she was spotted by [[Sekhar Kammula]], who gave her an acting offer, after seeing her performance in an audition. Accepting the offer, she made her acting debut in the 2007 Telugu film ''[[Happy Days (2007 film)|Happy Days]]'', enacting the role of Shravs. The film, upon release, became a blockbuster and won six awards at the 2008 [[Filmfare Awards South]], one of which was the [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress – Telugu|Award for Best Supporting Actress]] for Sonia for her performance that won her critical acclaim.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://awardsandwinners.com/category/filmfare-awards-south/2008/|title=Filmfare Awards South - 2008 {{!}} Winners & Nominees|website=awardsandwinners.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-14}}</ref>
In late 2008, her second film ''[[Vinayakudu (film)|Vinayakudu]]'' opposite [[Krishnudu]], one of her co-actors in ''Happy Days'', was released, which went on to become a successful venture as well. She soon got offers from the [[Tamil film industry]] as well and made her debut in Tamil with the [[N. Lingusamy]]-directed romantic-action film ''[[Paiyaa]]'' in 2010. That year she had another Tamil film releasing, ''[[Inidhu Inidhu]]'', a remake of ''Happy Days'', in which she reprised her role from the original.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/inidhu-inidhu-a-saga-so-sweet/article600430.ece |title=Inidhu Inidhu - A saga so sweet |publisher=The Hindu |date=2010-08-28 |accessdate=2016-12-04}}</ref> Sonia played the role of [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu|Samantha]]'s character's friend in the 2011 Telugu film ''[[Dookudu]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/sonia-got-a-chance-to-play-in-dookudu--malayalam-news-60875 |title=Sonia got a chance to play in Dookudu - Malayalam Movie News |publisher=Indiaglitz.com |date=2010-10-18 |accessdate=2016-12-04}}</ref>
She made her debut in [[Kannada]] with the film ''[[Ninnindale]]'' starring [[Puneeth Rajkumar]] and [[Erica Fernandes]], which was released in January 2014.<ref>{{cite web|author=Share on Twitter |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Sonia-going-places/articleshow/44940114.cms |title=Sonia going places - Times of India |publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=2014-10-26 |accessdate=2016-12-04}}</ref>
Just a day before a day before [[International Women's Day]] in 2015, she released a short film on her YouTube channel. Scripted by Megha Wali, this film was about questioning moral policing. It was well received on social media and appreciated by many stars including [[Ram Gopal Varma]] and [[Amitabh Bachchan]]. It was shot at Country Club in Hyderabad.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/sonia-deeptis-short-film-against-moral-policing-impresses-amitabh-bachchan-ram-gopal-varma-video-625940|title=Sonia Deepti's Short Film Against Moral Policing Impresses Amitabh Bachchan, Ram Gopal Varma [VIDEO]|last=Hooli|first=Shekhar H|work=International Business Times, India Edition|access-date=2017-09-14|language=en}}</ref>
